				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Magic and cold resistance in Vox Raids<a name="7228"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 03 10:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually, IMHO, those numbers are low.  You need to have your resist, with gear only, at 100 for both, prior to buffs and bard songs.  With the buffs and songs, you should be over 200+ for the raid.  This will definately improve your chances of staying alive significantly.  As a bard, you need it even more, since your resist song is a key factor for boosting your group's resist.  If you fall, then wham, your group loses 70+ resist, and those AoE's take hold.  There is a huge difference between a 150 resist and a 200+ resist, especially since they &quot;twinked&quot; mobs AoE/spell damage and resistances.
<br />

<br />
Yes, you do swap out all that nice armor for resist gear.  Resist will keep you alive, not AC, since if you are doing your job at a dragon raid, and not hitting the mob, you will not be attacked physically, unless things go bad.  Mages at the raid should be able to summon some resist gear as well.
<br />

<br />
I intimately know the pattern of Vox's and Naggy's belly from singing my heart out under their scaly arses too many times!
<br />

<br />
Nothing feels better than this...
<br />

<br />
you RESIST the Cold Breath
<br />
you RESIST the Cold Breath
<br />
You take 5 Points of damage from the Cold Breath</span></td>
