				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Magic and cold resistance in Vox Raids<a name="7233"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 03 12:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hehe, oh how true, I can tell you Ragefire's gender and can tell what it ate for breakfast how close I get to it's underbelly trying to keep the melee's alive for the COUNTLESS cleric epic raids I've been on.  SHEESH, I can't even get a group together for Phinny, but that's another story.
<br />

<br />
As for resists, all I can say is at 290something, I was still taking 200 or so damage per AoE from Ragefire last night.  Not enough to bother a raid buffed 3kish hps, but only 3 melee's went down (one ranger for outdamaging the MT early on, and a few that didn't bother with base resists and my song dropped when I was mezed or feared or something early on).  Moral of the story, get those resists over 100.
<br />

<br />
Sure it costs plat, doesn't everything?  I have roughly 3 full suits of armor for various occasions. It only bugs me when I am Main Looter and fill up all my bags too quick.  At minimum, pick up Blue Diamond rings and bracers (maybe earrings too) as they don't kill your stats as much and have nice resists to them.  If your guild has a GM Jeweler you can likely pick up each for about 400-500pp.  Not sure, I'm not one and haven't priced them in a while.
<br />

<br />
Oh and I completely agree with Robyn. If the bard goes down on a dragon raid, it's pretty much assured a wipe cause the healers can't keep all those melee's alive.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
