				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Magic and cold resistance in Vox Raids<a name="7458"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 20 03 9:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Aulinya,
<br />

<br />
I agree with the other posters that suggest you should not really worry about AC for Naggy and Vox.  I know that it is counter-intuitive to lower AC but for raids where you will not be meleeing or actually drawing any aggro except from your proximity to the mob, AC is unimportant.  Your AC only lowers the damage you take from melee, not from the dragon's AoE effects -- that is where resists kick in.  Your goal in the dragon raid is not to provide DPS, but to keep those that can alive.  Consequently, you are banging your drum and pumping resists.  If lag isn't too bad, you can twist in some other songs, but don't let the resist song drop.  When a mob is AoEing for 1100 pts a shot, I don't care whether your AC is 1000 or 600, you are on CR if the AoE is not resisted.  Yeah, it seems like you are not doing too much on the raid, but your group will be better for it.  Like the other posters said as well, you will end up carrying multiple sets of gear on certain days just to be safe.  Have fun and I hope you get your scale.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
